    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*duž-gauna-</w></mentioned>.
        Для второй части см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i ‘шерсть’. Первая часть,
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>duž-</w><gloss><q>дурной</q></gloss></mentioned> (в сложных словах), в
        современном осетинском уже не осмысляется; ср. живое образование fyd-q˳yn | fud-ǧun [см.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/>] буквально „дурношерстный“, ‘взъерошенный’.
        Древнеиранские сложные слова с %iduž-, duš%i- в первой части многочисленны: <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>duž-manah-</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>dušman</w><gloss><q>враг</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>duš-xvarəϑa-</w><gloss><q>дурная
            пища</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>duž-daenā-</w><gloss><q>следующий дурной религии</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>duž-dōiϑra-</w><gloss><q>имеющий дурной
            глаз</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>duž-vačah-</w><gloss><q>злоречивый</q></gloss></mentioned>, и др. Ср. также
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>dušman</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>dusnām</w></mentioned>, и др., <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>δuš-tuvān(δštw'n)</w><gloss><q>несчастный</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>duš-darrau-</w><gloss><q>имеющий злую
                волю</q></gloss></mentioned>. Наряду с %iduz-ǧun%i сохранилось другое сложное слово,
        составленное из тех же элементов, но в обратном порядке (инверсия): %iǧuntʼuz%i(←
        %iǧun-duz%i) ‘хмурый’, ‘взъерошенный’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yntʼyz"/> | %iǧuntʼuz%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fydq0yn"/> | %ifudǧun%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zyǧ0mmæ"/> |
                %iusqummæ%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
        /><biblScope>233</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
            ><lang/><w>*duž-gauna-</w></mentioned>. For the second part see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i ‘hair’. The second part, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>duž-</w><gloss><q>bad</q></gloss></mentioned> (in compounds),is no longer
        comprehended in modern Ossetic; cf. actual compound %ifyd-q˳yn%i | %ifud-ǧun%i [see <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/>] literally “bad-haired”, ‘messy’. Old Iranian
        compounds with %iduž-, duš%i- in the first part are numerous: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>duž-manah-</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>dušman</w><gloss><q>enemy</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>duš-xvarəϑa-</w><gloss><q>bad
            food</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>duž-daenā-</w><gloss><q>following bad religion</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>duž-dōiϑra-</w><gloss><q>having bad
            eye</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>duž-vačah-</w><gloss><q>evil-speaking</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. Cf. also
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>dušman</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>dusnām</w></mentioned>, etc., <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>δuš-tuvān(δštw'n)</w><gloss><q>unlucky</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>duš-darrau-</w><gloss><q>having bad
            will</q></gloss></mentioned>. Apart from %iduz-ǧun%i, there is another compound which
        has same elements but in an inverse order: %iǧuntʼuz%i(← %iǧun-duz%i) ‘gloomy’, ‘messy’. Cf.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yntʼyz"
        /> | %iǧuntʼuz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/> | %ifudǧun%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_zyǧ0mmæ"/> | %iusqummæ%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>233</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
